


	
        "Support our troops" wristbands provide only 1/3 support          Raymond Chen        
            
            February 28th, 20050 0
		
         Over at Slate, Timothy Noah notes  how much money from so-called “awareness bracelets” actually go to the causes they purport to champion. 
 In summary, 



Bracelet
Vendor
Cause
Portion thatbenefits cause


Yellow “Livestrong”
Lance Armstrong Foundation
supporting cancer survivors
all


Cinnamon
Tsunami Relief
Red Cross, UNICEF, CARE
1/2


Camo-green
7-11
USO
1/3


Light blue
Awareness Depot
Tsunami disaster relief (unspecified charity)
1/10


Yellow
Awareness Depot
Support our troops
0


 I find it ironic that the “Support our troops” bracelet doesn’t actually support our troops. And is  yellow really the right color to use to demonstrate support for the military? 

        
                

        
		
                

            
            
                
